@7215 = ~Dispel Magic~
@7216 = ~Dispel Magic (Abjuration)
Level: 2
Range: 0
Duration: special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

This spell allows the warlord to get rid of all magic effects that affect him. The spell can not be selective, and dissipates the effects created by spells, abilities, items, potions, etc... without distinction, whether they are harmful or not. So it's a spell to use wisely, because it can ruin a strategy of combat readiness.
When he castes Dispel Magic, the warlord has a base chance of successfully dispelling of 50%. For every level that the warlord of the dispel magic is above the original caster, his chance of success increases by 5%. For every level that the caster of dispel magic is below the original caster, his chance of success decreases by 10%. Thus, if he is of level 10 and tries to dispel a slow cast by a mage of level 12, he will have only 30% chance of success. On the opposite, if the mage who cast slow on warlord is of level 6, the latter will have a 70% chance to dispel the spell. In any case, there is always a 1% chance of success or failure of dispelling.~
